<br>
That night, all of my friends and family gathered in the hospital room.  My wife lay in the bed with him holding him as he occasionally shook and tremored.  We prayed, sincere honest prayer I poured out my soul to God.  My son's great-great grandmother anointed his head with blessed oil from her church.  And you know what?  About 5 minutes later my sons eyes fluttered..he relaxed..opened his eyes..looked at me and said &quot;Daddy..I'm thirsty&quot;.  I wept again.  His neurologist nearly fainted when she saw him the next day..all she could say was &quot;How.....what..how.?&quot;<br>
<br>
My son is about to be 4 years old.  He just learned the pledge of allegiance and The Lord's Prayer.  He's doing exceptionally well in school with no adverse affects.  Not bad for a child that was dead.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tell me there is no God now, I defy you to make me not believe in God. <br>
<br>
If you doubt this..you have only to ask my hotheaded friend and co-worker Trech..he was one of the people in the room when my son opened his eyes.<br>
<br>
Poppen Steelfist 54 Disciple and officer of SoD  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzariel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zariel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www." BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/18/01 9:10:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Belief in God</span><hr size=1> "Truth does not demand belief. Scientists do not join hands every Sunday, singing, "Yes, gravity is real! I will have faith! I will be strong! I believe in my heart that what goes up, up, up must come down, down, down. Amen!" If they did, we would think they were pretty insecure about it."<br>
<br>
Ever gone to holy services?  People don't go to services because they are "insecure" about their faith, and I wouldn't consider scientists insecure for professing their belief in gravity, either.  People go to a church, synagogue, mosque, sacred grove, or other religious space for many reasons.  They go for quiet, for consolation, to worship, to think, etc.  I think the main reason is to share the love and joy they feel in their religion with others, and to receive love and joy in return.  While one doesn't need to go to a sacred space and sing, it is a wonderful feeling to be with others who know G-d exists.<br>
Sorry to post twice in a row, but I had to respond to that.  Also, Poppen, thank you for sharing your story with us.  I have one similar, about a boy I knew from church, my pediatrician's son.  I am so glad your little boy is all right; that is truly the work of G-d.<br>
<br>
